@startuml

title Super Admin User Role and Status Update Sequence Diagram

actor "Super Admin" as Admin

participant "Frontend (Website)" as FE
participant "Apache\n(HTTP Server)" as Apache

box "Laravel Application" #LightGreen
  participant "Middleware" as MW
  participant "UserController" as UC
  participant "Eloquent ORM" as ORM
end box

database "MariaDB Database" as DB

note right of Admin
Super Admin can change user roles
and ban or unban user accounts
from the Search Users page.
They also have access to the
entire website.
end note

note left of DB
It is assumed the Super Admin is
authenticated/authorized unless an exception occurs.
end note


== Update User Role ==

Admin -> FE: Select new role and confirm role change
activate Admin
activate FE
activate Apache
activate MW
activate UC
activate ORM
activate DB

FE -> Apache: PUT /users/{user}/role

alt Route exists
    Apache -> MW: Forward HTTP role update request
else Route not found
    Apache --> FE: 404 Not Found
    FE --> Admin: Display "User role update route not found" error
end

alt Valid + Authorized
    MW -> UC: Pass authenticated and authorized role update request
else Validation/Auth error
    MW --> FE: 401 Unauthorized / 403 Forbidden / 422 Unprocessable Entity
    FE --> Admin: Display validation or authorization error
end

UC -> UC: Validate role in ['Usuario','Admin Inventario','Admin Mercado','Admin Facilidades','Admin Super']

alt Validation success
    UC -> ORM: Load User model from route binding
    ORM -> DB: SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ? LIMIT 1

    alt User found
        DB --> ORM: User record
        ORM --> UC: User retrieved

        UC -> ORM: user->save(role = request.role)
        ORM -> DB: UPDATE users SET role = ? WHERE id = ?

        alt Role update success
            DB --> ORM: Update successful
            ORM --> UC: User role persisted
            UC --> FE: Return JSON { message: 'Rol actualizado correctamente' }
            FE --> Admin: Show "Rol actualizado correctamente"
        else Role update failure
            DB --> ORM: Update failed / SQL exception
            ORM --> UC: User role update failed
            UC --> FE: 500 Internal Server Error
            FE --> Admin: Display system error while updating user role
        end

    else User not found
        DB --> ORM: Empty result set
        ORM --> UC: User not found
        UC --> FE: 404 Not Found
        FE --> Admin: Display selected user not found error
    end

else Validation failure
    UC --> FE: 422 Unprocessable Entity
    FE --> Admin: Display invalid role selection error
end


== Update User Status ==

Admin -> FE: Click ban/unban button and confirm action
FE -> Apache: PUT /users/{user}/status

alt Route exists
    Apache -> MW: Forward HTTP user status update request
else Route not found
    Apache --> FE: 404 Not Found
    FE --> Admin: Display "User status update route not found" error
end

alt Valid + Authorized
    MW -> UC: Pass authenticated and authorized status update request
else Validation/Auth error
    MW --> FE: 401 Unauthorized / 403 Forbidden / 422 Unprocessable Entity
    FE --> Admin: Display validation or authorization error
end

UC -> UC: Validate status in ['Activo','Bloqueado']

alt Validation success
    UC -> ORM: Load User model from route binding
    ORM -> DB: SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ? LIMIT 1

    alt User found
        DB --> ORM: User record
        ORM --> UC: User retrieved

        UC -> UC: previousStatus = user.status
        UC -> ORM: user->save(status = request.status)
        ORM -> DB: UPDATE users SET status = ? WHERE id = ?

        alt Status update success
            DB --> ORM: Update successful
            ORM --> UC: User status persisted
            UC --> FE: Return JSON { success, message, status }
            FE --> Admin: Show ban/unban success confirmation "La cuenta ha sido bloqueada/desbloqueada"
        else Status update failure
            DB --> ORM: Update failed / SQL exception
            ORM --> UC: User status update failed
            UC --> FE: 500 Internal Server Error
            FE --> Admin: Display system error while updating user status
        end

    else User not found
        DB --> ORM: Empty result set
        ORM --> UC: User not found
        UC --> FE: 404 Not Found
        FE --> Admin: Display selected user not found error
    end

else Validation failure
    UC --> FE: 422 Unprocessable Entity
    FE --> Admin: Display invalid status selection error
end

@enduml